## 11. Inherited ESLint Rules (portal code inherits these)

Portal code runs through three ESLint layers. Key rules agents must know:

| ID        | What                                                | Scope             | Impact on portal                                      |
| --------- | --------------------------------------------------- | ----------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| CIG-02    | No float math on money (`Number()`, `parseFloat()`) | Finance module    | Portal SCF / payments must use `convertAmountPrecise` |
| CIG-03    | No `req.query as Record` / `req.params` casts       | Finance module    | Portal routes must use Zod `.parse()`                 |
| CIG-04    | Routes/pages cannot import `@afenda/db` directly    | Base config (all) | Portal pages/routes use composition root only         |
| RBP-03    | Use `.toSorted()` not `.sort()`                     | Web app           | Portal list sorting must be immutable                 |
| RBP-CACHE | Server fetchers must use `cache()`                  | Web app           | Portal server fetchers need `cache()` wrapper         |

See `portal-ci-gates.mdc` for the complete inherited rule table.
